‚äïmeta‚äï
name = "archive-sky-workflow"
description = "Archive a .sky workflow into _archive/ with its trigger neutralized so it leaves the active path; reversible via restore mode. Manual gate before any move. Pure bash, no LLM."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
‚äï‚äï

¬ßfind¬ß
bash = "set -eu\nDIR=\"$SKY_DIR\"\nNAME=\"$SKY_NAME\"\nMODE=\"${SKY_MODE:-archive}\"\nif [ \"$MODE\" != \"archive\" ] && [ \"$MODE\" != \"restore\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: mode must be 'archive' or 'restore', got '$MODE'\" >&2\n  exit 1\nfi\nif [ \"$MODE\" = \"restore\" ]; then\n  SOURCE=\"$DIR/_archive/$NAME.sky\"\n  DEST=\"$DIR/$NAME.sky\"\nelse\n  SOURCE=\"$DIR/$NAME.sky\"\n  DEST=\"$DIR/_archive/$NAME.sky\"\nfi\nif [ ! -f \"$SOURCE\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: source not found: $SOURCE\" >&2\n  exit 1\nfi\nif [ -e \"$DEST\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: destination already exists: $DEST\" >&2\n  exit 1\nfi\necho \"mode=$MODE\"\necho \"source=$SOURCE\"\necho \"dest=$DEST\""
¬ß¬ß

¬ßgate¬ß
depends_on = ["find"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.prompt = "Confirm move. Archiving NEUTRALIZES the trigger so the file cannot auto-fire even if the loader scans _archive/. Restore returns it as a manual-only workflow (re-add a trigger to reactivate). Review the source and dest paths printed by the find step, then approve."
wait.timeout = "1h"
¬ß¬ß

¬ßmove¬ß
depends_on = ["gate"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash = "set -eu\nDIR=\"$SKY_DIR\"\nNAME=\"$SKY_NAME\"\nMODE=\"${SKY_MODE:-archive}\"\nif [ \"$MODE\" = \"restore\" ]; then\n  SOURCE=\"$DIR/_archive/$NAME.sky\"\n  DEST=\"$DIR/$NAME.sky\"\nelse\n  SOURCE=\"$DIR/$NAME.sky\"\n  DEST=\"$DIR/_archive/$NAME.sky\"\nfi\nif [ \"$MODE\" = \"archive\" ]; then\n  mkdir -p \"$DIR/_archive\"\n  grep -v '^trigger\\.' \"$SOURCE\" > \"$SOURCE.tmp\"\n  mv \"$SOURCE.tmp\" \"$SOURCE\"\nfi\nif command -v git >/dev/null 2>&1 && git -C \"$DIR\" rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  git -C \"$DIR\" mv \"$SOURCE\" \"$DEST\" || mv \"$SOURCE\" \"$DEST\"\nelse\n  mv \"$SOURCE\" \"$DEST\"\nfi\necho \"moved $SOURCE -> $DEST\""
¬ß¬ß

¬ßverify¬ß
depends_on = ["move"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash = "set -eu\nDIR=\"$SKY_DIR\"\nNAME=\"$SKY_NAME\"\nMODE=\"${SKY_MODE:-archive}\"\nif [ \"$MODE\" = \"restore\" ]; then\n  DEST=\"$DIR/$NAME.sky\"\nelse\n  DEST=\"$DIR/_archive/$NAME.sky\"\nfi\nif [ ! -f \"$DEST\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: moved file not found at $DEST\" >&2\n  exit 1\nfi\nsky lint \"$DEST\""
¬ß¬ß

‚Äª‚Äª
archive-sky-workflow
====================

Move a .sky workflow into an _archive/ subdir with its trigger neutralized so it
leaves the active load path, behind a manual gate. Reversible via restore mode.

Pure bash, no LLM: moving a file does not change its content, so the moved file
stays lint-clean and a bash `sky lint` verify suffices. No token cost.

What archiving does to the trigger
----------------------------------
Archiving STRIPS every `^trigger.` line from the file (grep -v) before the move.
This NEUTRALIZES the trigger, so even if the loader ever scans _archive/, the
file cannot auto-fire. Restore moves the file back but leaves the trigger
neutralized: it returns as a manual-only workflow. Re-add a trigger line to
reactivate it.

DAG
---
  find ‚îÄ‚îÄ> gate (manual) ‚îÄ‚îÄ> move ‚îÄ‚îÄ> verify

  find    resolve source/dest from mode; fail if source missing or dest exists
  gate    manual confirm (shows both paths via find output); 1h timeout
  move    archive: mkdir _archive, strip trigger lines, git mv (|| mv)
          restore: git mv (|| mv) back, trigger stays neutralized
  verify  sky lint the moved file at its new path; nonzero exit on failure

Run
---
  archive (default):
    sky run archive-sky-workflow --var dir=.sky/workflows --var name=old-flow
  restore:
    sky run archive-sky-workflow --var dir=.sky/workflows --var name=old-flow --var mode=restore

Vars
----
  dir   directory holding the workflow (e.g. .sky/workflows)        -> $SKY_DIR
  name  workflow filename without .sky (e.g. old-flow)              -> $SKY_NAME
  mode  archive | restore; default archive when unset              -> $SKY_MODE
‚Äª‚Äª
